Version 2.1, 5 February 2016
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Added support for automatic updates
[+] Customer meta fields can now be linked to merge tags
[+] Added supported WooCommerce and WordPress version checks and related notices
[*] Checkout checkbox now will not show up if user is already subscribed to the list
[*] Better language file loading: WP_LANG_DIR . "/woochimp/" now supported
[*] Scripts and styles now loaded only if needed on page
[*] Improved user interface
[*] Other minor improvements and bug fixes

Version 2.0.1, 2 November 2015
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Variations of product now can be added to conditions
[+] Added a label attribute to the text for the checkout checkbox
[*] Fixed issue with sets not saving correctly on "Automatic" tab
[*] Fixed bug which was affecting new sets with "Products in cart" condition
[*] Other minor bug fixes

Version 2.0, 24 September 2015
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] "Checkout" tab got split into two independent tabs - "Checkbox" and "Automatic"
[+] Order Meta and Static Values now supported in fields for both checkout tabs
[+] Added new conditions related to customer role
[+] On checkout it's now possible to select interest groups
[+] New option "Subscribe on payment received" added
[+] Ecommerce 360: new option to delete cancelled/refunded orders
[*] Product lists on settings page are loaded via AJAX search now
[*] WooChimp Log added to store errors returned from MailChimp's requests
[*] Other minor bug fixes and cosmetic changes

Version 1.4.3, 25 February 2015
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Added Checkout checkbox position woocommerce_after_checkout_billing_form
[-] Removed "Above checkout form" and "Below checkout form" checkbox positions
[*] Order date is now passed to MailChimp correctly (added property order_date)
[*] Fixed subscribe on checkout bug related to WordPress User ID field
[*] Improved performance on stores with thousands of products
[*] Fixed interest group selection bug
[*] Other minor bug fixes

Version 1.4.2, 20 August 2014
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[*] Minor bug fixes

Version 1.4.1, 19 August 2014
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[*] Fixed a bug with related to mc_cid and mc_eid cookies

Version 1.4, 13 August 2014
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Added more checkout opt-in checkbox positioning options
[*] Fixed Ecommerce360 functionality to associate orders with campaigns
[*] Increased MailChimp list limit that can be loaded
[*] Fixed infinite loop issue when 'ghost' categories are present

Version 1.3, 13 March 2014
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Implemented custom MailChimp API wrapper class
[+] Option to choose different checkout page checkbox position
[+] Option to subscribe users after order is marked as completed
[-] Removed standard MailChimp API wrapper which caused conflicts with other plugins
[*] JS/CSS file version numbers now automatically follow plugin version number

Version 1.2.1, 17 January 2014
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[-] Removed "Emails left" field from status page
[*] Minor bug fixes

Version 1.2, 14 January 2014
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Added support for conditional list and group selection
[+] Added PHP function to display signup forms
[*] Improved compatibility with other plugins
[*] Other minor bug fixes and improvements

Version 1.1, 8 November 2013
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Support for multiple groups for all subscription options
[+] Option to choose whether groups should be added or replaced
[+] Support for custom form fields that are linked with MailChimp's merge tags
[+] Option to pass customer details to MailChimp's merge tags on checkout
[+] Support for MailChimp Webhooks
[+] Option to skip subscription if user has unsubscribed from the same list
[+] Displaying more MailChimp status fields
[-] Removed first name and last name fields in favor of custom fields
[*] Fixed issues with frontend Ajax calls
[*] Improved admin interface usability

Version 1.0.1, 6 November 2013
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Added powerful styling features - skins, theme override and custom CSS
[*] Fixed a bug related to MailChimp API class loading
[*] Fixed several styling issues for signup forms
[*] Fixed a bug that prevented customers from using spaces in names when signing up
[*] Renamed plugin to WooChimp

Version 1.0, 5 November 2013
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
[+] Initial release
